We found no difference (F2,26 = 0.29, P = 0.75) in the days to return among the three age classes of great horned owls (Table 4). In addition, great horned owls translocated to the four distances returned to the airports during the same amount of time (F3,26 = 1.35, P = 0.28; Table 4). Thus, the number of days it took translocated great horned owls to return to an airfield following a mitigation translocation was not influenced by either age of the birds or the distance they were translocated.Table 4
